# RespMech golden-test transient output
tests/golden/_work/

# Production golden RAW DATA — never commit (repo is public): real recordings +
# Emil's expected output spreadsheets stay local. Only the derived, de-identified
# golden numbers (tests/golden/production_golden.json) and manifest are committed.
/tests/golden/production/*
!/tests/golden/production/README.md
tests/golden/_prod_work/

# CLINICAL / PATIENT DATA — never commit (repo is public). Belt-and-braces against an
# accidental `git add` of real recordings. The clinical examples live OUTSIDE this repo
# (../respmech-clinical-examples) and are not version-controlled; these patterns catch a
# copy of that folder, or stray recordings, if one ever lands inside the tree. The only
# CSVs that belong here are the synthetic goldens under tests/golden/input/ — raw patient
# CSV/TXT recordings must never be added anywhere else.
*clinical-examples/
clinical/
patient-data/
# raw recording binary formats — none are legitimate tracked files in this repo
*.mat
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.edf
*.adicht
*.adidat

# macOS
.DS_Store
tests/golden/_prod_work_newcore/
